WeRateDogs tweeted dog breed analysis¶

The WeRateDogs Twitter archive was run through a neural network that can classify breeds of dogs. I have a cat myself and don't know much about dogs. I found it would be interesting to look at the insights of WeRateDogs breeds. Since not all available data was run through the neural network some dog breeds are labeled as 'unknown' or unidentified - dogs images were not identified by the neural network.
The proportion of 'unknown' and 'unidentified' dog breeds together is 20.5%. 4/5 of data has an identified breed, so breed analysis could be performed. Only 23 (46.8%) of all dog breeds has a breed proportion of more than 1%. 32.7% of breeds have a proportion of less than 1% per breed. The golden retriever breed has the largest proportion of dogs - 7.2%.
Below you can see the proportion of different dog breeds.

It looks like retrievers are the most popular dogs to tweet. It made me interested to find out what the top 20 tweeted dogs are. Here are the results:

Top 20 most tweeted dog breeds ranging from 151 to 20 dogs per breed, with median 32 dogs.
It seemes that we have a wide variety of dogs. Owners have many different tastes. Our top dogs are golden retrievers, followed by labrador retrievers. Despite the size, chihuahuas, toy poodles and shih tzus jogalong. Now we will look at our underdogs:

There is not much difference in the range of the top 20 most tweeted dog breeds (1-3).
It seems that not all retrievers are popular, or are rare breeds. Anyway, curly-coated ones are in our bottom 20, together with a giant schnauzer and others I have never heard about.

Now let's look at our ratings. Here are our 20 top dogs:

The rating of the dogs ranges from 13 to 11.3. The mean is 11.8 out of 10. The top rated breed is bouvier des flandres.
As I can see, golden retrievers are still in the list, but some new breeds have appeared. Hmmm.
Rating is a very subjective metric, let's look at the public opinion:

The dog breed with the most favourites (21069) is the bedlington terrier although it only has 6 tweets. The golden retriever with 151 tweets, but 10397 favourites is in 20th place. Average favourites per top 20 breeds is 13268.
Guess what? The dog breed with the most retweets(6584) is the bedlington terrier as well, and the golden retriever did not get in the top 20. The cardigan breed has the least retweets(2993) out of the top 20 with 21 tweets. Average retweet number per breed is 3869.
Favorites or retweets - the public love the same breeds.

18 dogs got in both the retweets and favourites top 20. They are highly rated by public, with a high number of retweets and favourites. They are the afghan hound, bedlington terrier, black-and-tan coonhound, bouvier des flandres, cardigan, cocker spaniel, english springer, eskimo dog, flat-coated retriever, french bulldog, irish water spaniel, lakeland terrier, leonberg, mexican hairless, saluki, samoyed, standard poodle, whippet.
I am not surprised to find another retriever here - flat-coated. Honestly, I am flat coated myself so I prefer curly coated ones, or at least not bald ones.
Checking the WeRateDogs ratings against public preferences we can find out that our rater and the public have different views, obviously.
Only five dogs got in all top 20s. They are highly rated, with a high number of retweets and favourites. They are the bouvier des flandres, eskimo dog, irish water spaniel, leonberg, saluki, samoyed.

Honestly, I don't know any of these breeds. The one thing for sure is that the samoyed and the eskimo dog are from the top 20 tweeted breeds and the bouvier des flandres from the bottom 20.

The last thing to look at is a dog breed distribution. As expected, many dog breeds have under 10 breed associates on WeRateDogs, the majority have under 30 tweets with occasional exceptions like golden retrievers (151), labrador retrievers (106), chihuahuas (90) and pembrokes (94).

This is the end of my analysis. Hope you fond it interesting.

Golden retriever is the overall winner for me. What about yours?
